parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Nominative 2nd Person Singular
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.
Neuter diminutive of pais; a childling, i.e., an infant, or a half-grown boy or girl; figuratively, an immature Christian.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Passive - 2nd Person Singular
str2: (a) I call, summon, invite, (b) I call, name. Akin to the base of keleuo; to 'call'.
From a compound of pro and phemi; a foreteller; by analogy, an inspired speaker; by extension, a poet.
Highest, most high, the heights. Superlative from the base of hupsos; highest, i.e. the Supreme, or the heavens.
For. A primary particle; properly, assigning a reason.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Middle - 2nd Person Singular
str2: To precede, pass on before, go before. From pro and poreuomai; to precede.
Neuter of a compound of en and a derivative of optanomai; in the face of.
Lord, master, sir; the Lord. From kuros; supreme in authority, i.e. controller; by implication, Master.
To make ready, prepare. From hetoimos; to prepare.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive Masculine 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
A way, road, journey, path. Apparently a primary word; a road; by implication, a progress; figuratively, a mode or means.
